modules.description: This module encodes HTTP/2 headers using HPACK compression. It maintains a dynamic table for reference and provides functions to initialize the encoder, set its memory capacity, and encode individual headers into a Faraday buffer. It is used to efficiently compress HTTP/2 header fields before transmission.

This module manages HPACK decoding with dynamic table capacity control. It provides functions to initialize and adjust the decoder's memory capacity, and to decode HPACK-encoded header blocks into lists of headers. It works directly with HPACK header blocks and dynamic tables, used in HTTP/2 header decompression workflows.

This module implements HPACK compression for HTTP/2 headers, providing encoding and decoding operations using dynamic tables. It handles header compression with memory-constrained tables, supporting incremental encoding into Faraday buffers and decoding from byte sequences into header lists. Concrete use cases include compressing and decompressing HTTP/2 header blocks during request/response processing in HTTP/2 clients and servers.
